# src/application/

The **application layer** — use cases, orchestration, and transaction
boundaries. Knows the domain; does not know HTTP, the database driver, or
the UI framework.

Belongs here:
- Application services / use-case handlers (one per user-facing intent)
- Command and query handlers
- Transaction / unit-of-work coordination
- Cross-aggregate workflows
- Authorization at the use-case level (the domain layer enforces invariants;
  the application layer enforces "is this user allowed to do this")

Does **not** belong here:
- Business rules — those belong on entities/aggregates in `../domain/`
- Wire formats, request parsing, view models — those go in `../presentation/`
- Concrete repository implementations — those go in `../infrastructure/`

Canonical reference: `{{ ai_folder }}/instructions/general/architecture.md`.
